cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on data confidentiality and encryption in cloud storage.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses cloud data storage services and their practicality.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper uses Intel SGX technology for file encryption and creates a virtual file system.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the storage and retrieval of encrypted data.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper integrates an Intel SGX application with the Cryptomator software.
